benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/tags - Retrieve payment tags

covered: GET Method - Valid Request: Scenarios cover successful retrievals for existing payments with various query parameter configurations.
GET Method - Empty Response: Scenario for no tags returns an empty JSON array (TC06).
Query Parameters - Comprehensive coverage: Tests exercise includedDeleted, pluginProperty and audit, including combinations (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC11).
Authorization - Access control: Tests validate proper handling of missing authentication token results in HTTP 401 (TC09).

Error Handling - HTTP error responses: Tests verify 400 for invalid IDs (TC08) and invalid parameters (TC10), 404 for non-existent payments (TC07, TC20), 500 for server errors (TC24), and 503 when a dependent service is down (TC13).
Security - Input validation: Tests verify protection against SQL injection in paymentId (TC15) and XSS in pluginProperty (TC16).
Edge/Size and Boundary: Tests for maximum allowed pluginProperty entries (TC17) and large payloads (TC18).
State & Data Variation: Tests for partially populated databases (TC19) and empty database (TC20) and for deleted tags (TC14) when includedDeleted=true.
Resilience & Recovery: Test simulate transient network failure and recovery (TC21).
Backward Compatibility: Compatibility with older clients (TC22).
Accessibility: Screen reader friendly response structure (TC23).
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination for large datasets.
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests for HTTP caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
Authorization Depth: No tests for 403 due to insufficient permissions or invalid tokens beyond missing token.
Concurrency & Ordering: No tests for concurrent updates or deterministic ordering of Tag objects.
recommendations: Add pagination tests to verify paging mechanics and performance with large tag sets.
Add authorization tests for invalid/expired tokens and insufficient permissions (403).
Add rate limiting tests to ensure stability under bursts and high load scenarios.
Add caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control behavior and conditional requests for tag data.
Add concurrency tests to simulate race conditions on tag reads/writes and ensure deterministic ordering of Tag objects.
Expand security tests with additional injection/XSS scenarios and stronger input validation.
